# harness: atomic-write temps (TASKS.json + the owner-overlay files never keep a crashed-mid-write file)
.harness/tracking/*.tmp
.harness/tracking/*.tmp.*

# harness: ideas->tasks pipeline — ephemeral per-sweep scratch (the IDEAS.jsonl inbox itself IS
# committed, so the inbox travels with the repo; the per-agent scratch dirs are ignored ENTIRELY —
# not just *.json — so a stray .md / .tmp / any incidental file an agent drops there can never be
# committed. The committed .gitkeep keeps each dir present in a fresh clone.
.harness/.pending-tasks/*
!.harness/.pending-tasks/.gitkeep
.harness/.pending-questions/*
!.harness/.pending-questions/.gitkeep

# harness: scope-gap dismissals — check-task-scope.sh's per-task "already reviewed, false positive"
# record, written by fix-scope-gaps. Local scratch, same shape as the pending-tasks/pending-questions
# dirs above: never committed, invalidated by content (a specHash mismatch), not by deletion.
.harness/.scope-gap-ignores/*
!.harness/.scope-gap-ignores/.gitkeep
